    "core_content": {
      "parsing_res_list": [
        {
          "block_label": "text",
          "block_content": "考点：考查介词短语辨析。",
          "block_bbox": [
            150,
            164,
            693,
            214
          ],
          "block_id": 0,
          "block_order": 1
        },
        {
          "block_label": "text",
          "block_content": "37.Please don't make so much noise. I hear the speaker very well.",
          "block_bbox": [
            161,
            381,
            1606,
            438
          ],
          "block_id": 1,
          "block_order": 2
        },
        {
          "block_label": "text",
          "block_content": "A. needn't B. mustn't C. can't D. shouldn't ",
          "block_bbox": [
            165,
            485,
            1872,
            549
          ],
          "block_id": 2,
          "block_order": 3
        },
        {
          "block_label": "text",
          "block_content": "【答案】C ",
          "block_bbox": [
            188,
            608,
            399,
            660
          ],
          "block_id": 3,
          "block_order": 4
        },
        {
          "block_label": "text",
          "block_content": "【解析】",
          "block_bbox": [
            190,
            716,
            350,
            765
          ],
          "block_id": 4,
          "block_order": 5
        },
        {
          "block_label": "text",
          "block_content": "试题分析：句意：请不要发出那么多的声响。我不能很好的听到演讲者讲话。A.neednt不必，不需要；B.mustmnt千万别，一定不要，表示禁止的意思；C.can't不能；D.shouldnt不应该。结合句意，可知是不能听到演讲者讲话，故选C。\n",
          "block_bbox": [
            182,
            805,
            2325,
            1093
          ],
          "block_id": 5,
          "block_order": 6
        },
        {
          "block_label": "text",
          "block_content": "考点：考查情态动词辨析。",
          "block_bbox": [
            176,
            1177,
            709,
            1228
          ],
          "block_id": 6,
          "block_order": 7
        },
        {
          "block_label": "text",
          "block_content": "38.  —Look at the stone bridge! Do you know it was built?",
          "block_bbox": [
            177,
            1397,
            1465,
            1445
          ],
          "block_id": 7,
          "block_order": 8
        },
        {
          "block_label": "text",
          "block_content": "--In the1860s. It's quite old.",
          "block_bbox": [
            227,
            1510,
            750,
            1558
          ],
          "block_id": 8,
          "block_order": 9
        },
        {
          "block_label": "text",
          "block_content": "A. when B. how C. where D. why ",
          "block_bbox": [
            179,
            1614,
            1785,
            1663
          ],
          "block_id": 9,
          "block_order": 10
        },
        {
          "block_label": "text",
          "block_content": "【答案】A ",
          "block_bbox": [
            202,
            1731,
            413,
            1780
          ],
          "block_id": 10,
          "block_order": 11
        },
        {
          "block_label": "text",
          "block_content": "【解析】",
          "block_bbox": [
            202,
            1838,
            361,
            1887
          ],
          "block_id": 11,
          "block_order": 12
        },
        {
          "block_label": "text",
          "block_content": "试题分析：句意：看那座石桥！你知道它是在什么时间被建造的吗？--在十九世纪六十年代。它相当古老了。A.when什么时间，何时；B.how怎么，如何；C.where在哪里；D.why为什么。根据回答的是时间，故选A。\n",
          "block_bbox": [
            184,
            1932,
            2316,
            2205
          ],
          "block_id": 12,
          "block_order": 13
        },
        {
          "block_label": "text",
          "block_content": "考点：考查连词。",
          "block_bbox": [
            187,
            2265,
            536,
            2311
          ],
          "block_id": 13,
          "block_order": 14
        },
        {
          "block_label": "text",
          "block_content": "39.Don't hurry him. You will just have to be and wait until he finishes the work.",
          "block_bbox": [
            184,
            2480,
            1874,
            2529
          ],
          "block_id": 14,
          "block_order": 15
        },
        {
          "block_label": "text",
          "block_content": "A. active B. careful C. patient D. famous ",
          "block_bbox": [
            184,
            2591,
            1850,
            2636
          ],
          "block_id": 15,
          "block_order": 16
        },
        {
          "block_label": "text",
          "block_content": "【答案】C ",
          "block_bbox": [
            201,
            2696,
            412,
            2746
          ],
          "block_id": 16,
          "block_order": 17
        },
        {
          "block_label": "text",
          "block_content": "【解析】",
          "block_bbox": [
            202,
            2801,
            361,
            2850
          ],
          "block_id": 17,
          "block_order": 18
        },
        {
          "block_label": "text",
          "block_content": "试题分析：句意：不要催他。你就是要有耐心等候，直到他完成这项工作。A.active积极的；B.careful仔细的，认真的；C.patient 有耐心的；D.famous著名的，出名的。根据上文不要催，及后文的等候，可知是有耐心的，故选C。\n",
          "block_bbox": [
            180,
            2910,
            2315,
            3168
          ],
          "block_id": 18,
          "block_order": 19
        },
        {
          "block_label": "text",
          "block_content": "考点：考查形容词辨析。",
          "block_bbox": [
            180,
            3224,
            669,
            3274
          ],
          "block_id": 19,
          "block_order": 20
        }
      ],
      "markdown": "考点：考查介词短语辨析。\n\n37.Please don't make so much noise. I hear the speaker very well.\n\nA. needn't B. mustn't C. can't D. shouldn't \n\n【答案】C \n\n【解析】\n\n试题分析：句意：请不要发出那么多的声响。我不能很好的听到演讲者讲话。A.neednt不必，不需要；B.mustmnt千万别，一定不要，表示禁止的意思；C.can't不能；D.shouldnt不应该。结合句意，可知是不能听到演讲者讲话，故选C。\n\n\n\n考点：考查情态动词辨析。\n\n38.  —Look at the stone bridge! Do you know it was built?\n\n--In the1860s. It's quite old.\n\nA. when B. how C. where D. why \n\n【答案】A \n\n【解析】\n\n试题分析：句意：看那座石桥！你知道它是在什么时间被建造的吗？--在十九世纪六十年代。它相当古老了。A.when什么时间，何时；B.how怎么，如何；C.where在哪里；D.why为什么。根据回答的是时间，故选A。\n\n\n\n考点：考查连词。\n\n39.Don't hurry him. You will just have to be and wait until he finishes the work.\n\nA. active B. careful C. patient D. famous \n\n【答案】C \n\n【解析】\n\n试题分析：句意：不要催他。你就是要有耐心等候，直到他完成这项工作。A.active积极的；B.careful仔细的，认真的；C.patient 有耐心的；D.famous著名的，出名的。根据上文不要催，及后文的等候，可知是有耐心的，故选C。\n\n\n\n考点：考查形容词辨析。",
